<br>
As for being tied to wandering skeletons, my only information on that comes from hearsay and a shaman quest.  Here's what I posted on my guild board when I tried to force-spawn Miragul:<br>
<br>
"As part of the totemic helm quest (shaman armor), you have to kill a Glacier Bear that pops in the caverns. The bear is supposedly the rare spawn in a wandering icebone-Lich-Bear spawn rotation with each MOB spawning 6-7 hours apart once the cycle has been started. Of course, since it's a shaman quest most respondents discussed, there was little detail on the lich, except that he's a tough bird. I killed the Glacier Bear and the other Icebones on Saturday at 7:30 a.m. PST. When I ran a druid over there on Saturday night, there were only three static (non-PH) Icebones, no bear, and no lich. But by then, the cycle was probably messed up, as the reports are that the spawned MOBs only stay up for 30 minutes."<br>
<br>
The glacier bear was about as rare as dirt.  I didn't devote much time to the force-spawn method becase I started the cycle on Saturday, and there had been a patch the previous Monday.  Therefore, I could mess around with a putative force-spawn method or wait two days for a natural spawn.  I decided to wait.  The lich spawned on Monday, and we whacked him.  Miragul stayed up for much longer than 30 minutes.  Of course, that could have been the "natural" version of him instead of the spawned version.<br>
<br>
If you want details on the totemic helm quest, go to Allakhazam's and look it up.  It talks about the spawn cycle in greater depth.<br>
<br>
On the other points.  Lifetap is 1500 points.  I ought to know--I took two of them.  I don't recall specific spells that he cast beyond the lifetap.  He's a necromancer, so expect the necro line of spells.  He may have cast a dot or two on me, but it wasn't serious enough to worry about, especially with a pair of CH clerics.<br>
<br>
You can kill him with a single group in the mid- to upper-50's, easy.  We did it with two groups just because extra people wanted to come help me with my epic.  Two clerics, two paladins, one shaman, one druid, one wizard, one enchanter, one warrior.  An enchanter is an absolute necessity (so you can turn in the phylactery).  Get the highest level enchanter possible.  Of course, it's completely doable with a level 50 enchanter.  I don't know if a bard could charm him, but I suppose it's possible.  You'd have to be really fast, though, since bard charms don't last very long.  A single cleric to CH a main tank be just fine.  His pet is more of an annoyance, so you can just root it or fear it away.  <br>
<br>
Standard MT strategy works well on this one.  His melee output isn't too high, so you won't need a CH rotation.  The lifetap does hurt, to try to get your highest HP tank to take the hit.<br>
